        "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
        "score": 1,
        "is_accepted": true,
        "last_activity_date": 1377668038,
        "creation_date": 1377668038,
        "body": "<p>Use ternary operator and <a href=\"http://static.springsource.org/spring/docs/3.0.x/reference/expressions.html#d0e11977\" rel=\"nofollow\">static method call<\/a><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>#{jobParameters['something']==null?(double)0:T(java.lang.Double).valueOf(jobParameters['something'])}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>be carefull because, if jobParameters['something'] is not rappresenting a valid double you will get a <code>NumberFormatException<\/code>.<br/>\nYou can think to use a function like <a href=\"http://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/javadocs/api-2.6/org/apache/commons/lang/math/NumberUtils.html#toDouble%28java.lang.String%29\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>NumberUtils.toDouble()<\/code><\/a> that doesn't throw exception, but set a default value.<\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 18480093,
        "question_id": 18478629
    }],
